Package exe.bbllw8.either

Class Either<A,B>

java.lang.Object
exe.bbllw8.either.Either<A,B>
Type Parameters:
A - Type of the left value
B - Type of the right value
Direct Known Subclasses:
Left, Right
public abstract class Either<A,B> extends Object
Represents a value of 1 of 2 possible types (disjoint union).

null values are not accepted and will throw exceptions if used in an Either instance.

Construct an instance using one of:

  • Left: instance with a left value
  • Right: instance with a right value
  • from(boolean, Supplier, Supplier): instance from the evaluation of a supplied boolean value

This class is not serializable.

Since:
1.0.0

    • joinLeft

      public static <B, C> Either<C,B> joinLeft(Either<Either<C,B>,B> either)
      Joins an Either through Left.

      This method requires that the left side of this Either is itself an Either type. That is, this must be some type like: Either<Either<C, B>, B>

      If this instance is a Left<Either<C, B>> then the contained Either<C, B> will be returned, otherwise this value will be returned unmodified.

      Since:
      2.0.0

    • joinRight

      public static <A, C> Either<A,C> joinRight(Either<A,Either<A,C>> either)
      Joins an Either through Right.

      This method requires that the left side of this Either is itself an Either type. That is, this must be some type like: Either<A, Either<A, C>>

      If this instance is a Right<Either<A, C>> then the contained Either<A, C> will be returned, otherwise this value will be returned unmodified.

      Since:
      2.0.0
